  "texts": [
    "However, the semantic relations in WordNet don't capture the semantic relationships associated with proper nouns, and temporal and location arguments [17].",
    "The personalized KGs [27] group nodes and edges into \"super nodes\" and \"super edges,\" which yields promising results in adaptive summarization.",
    "The RDFbased Query-oriented summarization approach presented by [36] identifies the nodes with shared ingoing and outgoing edges as equivalence classes and groups those as supernodes.",
    "Even though this approach lowers overall storage costs, the modeling errors are high.",
    "The FACES approach [14] in singleentity summarization considers the popularity, uniqueness, and diversity of facts to identify imperative facts."
  ],
